			<ns0:name>cbiffle@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/cbiffle@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
We have well-defined code review processes and practices, but they're basically an oral tradition.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
As we grow (both Googlers and external committers), it becomes more important to document this stuff -- particularly aspects like committing to the TCB and why it's different.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
We need both a HOWTO for committers, and a general document providing rationale and details.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-02-24T23:37:14.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-06-24T06:28:02.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:cc>
